* One-off install to enable building of packages:
  sudo apt install python3-all

* Change version number in:
  - setup.py

* In debian_wheezy/changelog and debian_stretch/changelog
  - Update version numbers
  - Update timestamp

* Make sure that the project builds successfully using python3 setup.py build

* Commit your changes to github

* Run ./make_deb

* Debian packages will appear in the dist/ directory

* Build on a wheezy system to create wheezy packages, a squeeze system
  for squeeze packages
